<HL>
   Idemitsu Kosan Unit Venture
</HL>
<DATE>
07/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   J.IKC EUROP REP
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Idemitsu Petrochemical Co. and Repsol Quimica
S.A. have agreed to a joint venture to produce polystyrene in
Spain, an Idemitsu official said Monday. The venture will be
owned equally by the two parents.
   Idemitsu Petrochemical is a subsidiary of Idemitsu Kosan
Co., a major privately held oil company. Repsol Quimica is a
unit of Repsol S.A., the Spanish state oil company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The venture is due to begin production in the second half
of 1992 at an output of 50,000 tons a year, the official
said.
   Idemitsu expects to sell a large part of the production to
Japanese household appliance makers operating in Europe,
according to the official. Polystyrene is the basic material
of the shells of most appliances.
</TEXT>
