WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS I.CIR
</CO>
<LP>
   MILAN -- Rodolfo De Benedetti, the eldest son of Italian
financier Carlo De Benedetti, was named general manager of
Cie. Industriali Riunite S.p.A. (CIR), the family's key
industrial holding company.
   The younger Mr. De Benedetti, 29 years old, will succeed
Corrado Passera in this chief operating position at CIR, the
company said. Mr. Passera resigned from CIR two weeks after
he was named general manager of Arnoldo Mondadori Editore
S.p.A., a publishing company controlled by CIR.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Rodolfo De Benedetti, who was general manager of the
family financial holding concern Cofide S.p.A. and already a
CIR boardmember, was appointed to his new post by CIR's board
of directors Monday, the statement said.
   Rodolfo De Benedetti has a degree in political economy and
law from the University of Geneva. He started his career in
finance in 1985 with Lombard Odier in Geneva, and in 1987 he
worked with Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. in New York.
   In 1988 he became director of international affairs at
Cofide before he was appointed general manager in April 1989.
He will leave his post at Cofide as a result of the new
appointment. Mr. De Benedetti is married and has two
children.
